\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012MnfWPZabGmuZ3Dii26SC9\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Fix E2E (and agent-integration) Plugin Subcommand Visibility\\n     2→\\n     3→## Context\\n     4→\\n     5→The `/e2e` skill works (auto-discovered from `.claude/skills/e2e/SKILL.md`), but subcommands like `/e2e:debug`, `/e2e:triage-ci`, `/e2e:implement` are invisible. They're defined as plugin commands in `.claude/plugins/e2e/commands/`, but local project plugins aren't auto-discovered — only marketplace-installed plugins get loaded.\\n     6→\\n     7→The `agent-integration` plugin has the same problem.\\n     8→\\n     9→The original plan's Step 1 (`/plugin marketplace add ./.claude/plugins/e2e`) failed because each individual plugin directory isn't a marketplace — a marketplace is a **container** with a `marketplace.json` that lists plugins.\\n    10→\\n    11→## Approach: Create a local marketplace wrapping both plugins\\n    12→\\n    13→A marketplace needs a `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` file that catalogs plugins with relative source paths. We'll make `.claude/plugins/` itself a marketplace containing both plugins, then register it via `extraKnownMarketplaces` + `enabledPlugins` in `.claude/settings.json` so it's automatic for all team members.\\n    14→\\n    15→## Steps\\n    16→\\n    17→### 1. Create marketplace.json\\n    18→\\n    19→Create `.claude/plugins/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`:\\n    20→\\n    21→```json\\n    22→{\\n    23→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire-dev-tools\\\",\\n    24→  \\\"owner\\\": {\\n    25→    \\\"name\\\": \\\"Entire Team\\\"\\n    26→  },\\n    27→  \\\"plugins\\\": [\\n    28→    {\\n    29→      \\\"name\\\": \\\"e2e\\\",\\n    30→      \\\"source\\\": \\\"./e2e\\\",\\n    31→      \\\"description\\\": \\\"E2E test triage, debugging, and fix implementation toolkit\\\"\\n    32→    },\\n    33→    {\\n    34→      \\\"name\\\": \\\"agent-integration\\\",\\n    35→  